2000-05-29 15:40  thomas

	* zipios++/fcollexceptions.h: The copy constructors for all three
	defined exception types were marked with explicit, which they
	really shouldn't be, and which gcc 2.95.2 really didn't like.
	
	Zipios++ has now been tested and found to work on
	
	Mandrake linux	 / gcc 2.95.2
	
	and
	
	RedHat 6.2 linux / egcs-2.91.66

2000-05-29 15:23  thomas

	* zipios++/simplesmartptr.h: Changed the SimpleSmartPointer class
	template, such that it doesn't need to be an unbound friend with
	itself, which some compilers don't support. Now it relies on that
	SimpleSmartPointer only has one real resource, ie. the real
	pointer, and this resource is available directly through the
	SimpleSmartPointer::get() method.

